The problem is to prove an identity involving sums and products of Riemann sums. The key is to carefully manipulate the expression on the left-hand side to match the right-hand side. 

The left-hand side (LHS) is:

`(b - a) / ‚ÜĎ(n * k) * ‚ąĎ j ‚ąą Finset.range n, ‚ąĎ k_1 ‚ąą Finset.range k, f (a + (‚ÜĎ(j + k_1 * n) + 1) * (b - a) / ‚ÜĎ(n * k)) - (b - a) / ‚ÜĎn * ‚ąĎ i ‚ąą Finset.range n, f (a + (‚ÜĎi + 1) * (b - a) / ‚ÜĎn)`

The right-hand side (RHS) is:

`(b - a) / ‚ÜĎn * ‚ąĎ j ‚ąą Finset.range n, (1 / ‚ÜĎk * ‚ąĎ ‚Ąď ‚ąą Finset.range k, f (a + (‚ÜĎ‚Ąď + ‚ÜĎj * ‚ÜĎk + 1) * (b - a) / (‚ÜĎn * ‚ÜĎk)) - f (a + (‚ÜĎj + 1) * (b - a) / ‚ÜĎn))`

